## 2. Anchor MSME

### Who you are
A large buyer — an auto-ancillary or manufacturing corporate — who purchases from MSME vendors and is the counterparty on the invoices vendors want financed.

### Your role is mostly passive — but critical

You don't log into this platform day-to-day. Your involvement happens through systems you already use:

1. **GST portal (IMS):** When your accounts team receives an e-invoice from a vendor, actively clicking **"Accept"** on the GST Invoice Management System is what unlocks Kind 1 attestation for that invoice. Leaving it as "pending" or letting it default to "deemed accepted" (no action taken) weakens the vendor's application — deemed-accepted invoices are flagged as a lower-confidence signal to lenders.
2. **Repayment routing:** Ops sets up a confirmed repayment channel with you once during onboarding — this is what lets the platform (and lenders) know that when a loan is disbursed against your invoice, you will pay it back through a verified route directly to the lender, not through any pooled account controlled by the platform. This is a regulatory requirement (RBI Digital Lending Directions 2025 prohibit any pass-through pooling).

### Onboarding (done by ops, not self-service)

Ops onboards you via:
```
POST /ops/anchor/onboard   (ops-only, requires anchor-manager or platform-admin role)
{
  "name": "Anchor Company Name",
  "gstin": "36AABCY9234H1Z5",
  "sector": "Automotive",
  "region": "Western Maharashtra",
  "onboarded_by": "ops_manager@company.com"
}
→ { "anchor_id": "<uuid>", "status": "onboarded" }
```
There's no anchor self-service portal today — reach out to the platform's ops/relationship team to get set up, or to update your sector/region metadata.

### What you'll notice operationally

- **When you accept an invoice on GST IMS**, that action is what your vendor is waiting on before they can get financed.
- **When a loan is disbursed** against your invoice, the repayment obligation and schedule are between you and the lender directly — the platform is never in that money-movement path.
- Ops staff can see your onboarding status, sector, and region in the {{BACK_OFFICE_NAME}}, alongside every vendor and loan tied to you.

