## 5. Admin (`platform-admin`)

### Who you are
Someone with full platform administration rights — typically a senior ops lead, a compliance officer, or platform engineering.

### What only you can do (beyond ops staff)

| Area | What |
|---|---|
| **User & role management** | In Keycloak (realm `ocen-platform`), create staff accounts and assign roles: `platform-admin`, `operations`, `anchor-manager`, `lender-viewer`. |
| **DPDP Data Subject Rights** | `POST /dpdp/rights/submit` (access / erasure / correction / grievance / nomination requests) and `GET /dpdp/rights/{request_id}` to check status — 72-hour SLA, fulfilled via a Temporal workflow. |
| **Consent verification** | `GET /dpdp/consent/{data_principal_id}` — check what a data principal has consented to. |
| **Breach monitoring** | The platform watches for bulk PII access (>100 reads/5 min), repeated failed auth (>20/10 min), and exports without a DSR (>1/min). Confirmed breaches trigger a Temporal workflow and a DPBI notification obligation within 72 hours. |
| **Audit verification** | Every D0–D3 decision produces a signed, chain-linked receipt (`ruleset_hash`, `input_hash`, KMS/HMAC signature). You can verify the hash chain hasn't been tampered with for regulatory inquiries. |
| **Decision rule changes** | Rules live as JSON (JDM format) in `rules/`, e.g. `rules/d0-kind1-gate.json`, `rules/d1-data-sufficiency.json`, `rules/d2-derived-flags.json`, `rules/d3-lender-prescreen.json`. Editing thresholds (e.g. tightening D1's "6 months of data" requirement) needs zero code deploys — the engine hot-reloads. |
| **DPDP config** | `dpdp_config.yaml` controls RBAC endpoint-role mappings, retention policies, breach thresholds, and consent purposes — all policy-as-config, no code changes. |
| **Brand/theme** | `brand/brand.yaml` is the single source of truth for the platform's name, logo, and color palette (currently "{{PRODUCT_NAME}}" — a working title). Regenerate and redeploy with `make brand-deploy`; see §6. |

### RBAC endpoint map (for reference)

| Path prefix | Allowed roles |
|---|---|
| `/ops/hold`, `/ops/release`, `/ops/flag`, `/ops/escalate` | `platform-admin`, `operations` |
| `/ops/applications/*` | `platform-admin`, `operations`, `lender-viewer` |
| `/ops/vendor/invite`, `/ops/anchor/onboard` | `platform-admin`, `anchor-manager` |
| `/dpdp/rights`, `/dpdp/consent` | `platform-admin` only |

RBAC is **disabled by default** in dev (`DPDP_RBAC_ENABLED=false`) — turn it on for staging/production.

### System monitoring

- `GET /health` on the borrower gateway checks Temporal connectivity.
- `backoffice_sync` consumer logs show any failed webhook deliveries to {{BACK_OFFICE_NAME}} (retries with exponential backoff, then dead-letters).
- Breach detection and DSR fulfillment both run as Temporal workflows — visible in the Temporal UI.

### Deployment footprint you're responsible for

| Service | Port | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `borrower-gateway` | 8000 | Main API — vendor, ops, DPDP, and OCEN callback endpoints |
| `ddp-engine` | 8001 | Derived data computation |
| `vdp-wedge` | 8002 | Invoice ingestion / Kind 1 checks |
| `trust-graph-api` | 8003 | Proprietary trust scoring |
| `la-orchestrator-worker` | — | Temporal worker running the loan origination pipeline |
| {{BACK_OFFICE_NAME}} | 80 (13.234.12.74) | Ops UI, themed with `munimco_brand` |
| Borrower PWA | 3000 (proxied via nginx) | Vendor-facing web app |

