## 6. Shared Concepts Glossary

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Kind 1 attestation** | Valid IRN + GST IMS "Accept" by anchor + active repayment routing. The core trust signal. |
| **IRN** | Invoice Reference Number — a 64-character SHA-256 hash from the GST e-invoicing portal. |
| **IMS** | Invoice Management System — the GST portal feature where anchors Accept/Reject/leave-Pending an invoice. |
| **D0–D3** | The platform's own decision gates (Kind 1 gate, data sufficiency, derived attributes, lender pre-screen). |
| **D4** | The lender's own underwriting decision — never made by this platform. |
| **Decision receipt** | A signed, content-addressed record of a rule evaluation — the audit trail. |
| **Trust Graph** | The platform's proprietary layer correlating attestation + origination + repayment across every anchor and lender — no single lender can replicate this view. |
| **OCEN 4.0** | India's Open Credit Enablement Network — the protocol connecting this Loan Agent to multiple lenders via a single integration. |
| **DPDP** | India's Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023 — governs consent, PII handling, retention, and breach response on this platform. |
| **AA** | Account Aggregator — the consent-based framework used to fetch a vendor's bank statements and GST data. |

